## TEMPLATE DOCUMENTS AND COUNTRY LOCALIZATION

LICENSE, service-terms, and related files in the DLE repository are **standard
 template documents** of the copyright holder. They do not replace a mandatory
 purchase or license agreement in a specific country.

**In each country:**

- An **Authorized Contributor** adapts terms to local law (taxes, currency,
  refunds, personal data, consumer protection, language, seller details).
- The customer enters into a contract with the **Contributor in their
  jurisdiction** (or with the Author if direct sale is explicitly offered).
- **Governing law and disputes** are defined in the **local contract** with
  the Contributor, unless otherwise agreed in writing with the Author.

**Unchanged in all jurisdictions** (unless a local contract explicitly grants
 the customer additional rights):

- copyright in the **initial (baseline) code** of DLE — **Alexander V. Tarabanov**
  (or successor upon notice, see below);
- copyright in **Contributor Updates** — the Contributor, with the **Author’s
  right of first refusal** on disposal (CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE § 4);
- no resale of source code to third parties;
- source code modification — Authorized Contributors only;
- royalty to Author **1,000 / 10,000 USDT** per license, paid upon written
  request (CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE § 3).

Localized service-terms may be published by Contributors on hb3-accelerator.com
 or in the data room for the relevant country.

